<TITLE> Benazir slaying is very tragic: Iftekhar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 28 (bdnews24.com)  Foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Friday termed Benazir Bhutto's killing 'very tragic' and condemned the assassination of the former prime minister of Pakistan. "The aspiration of a nation cannot be hostage to the bullet of assassins," Iftekhar told journalists after attending a discussion meeting at Brac Inn Centre in the city. He hoped that the black clouds over Pakistan's political horizon would soon disperse and the people of the country would overcome the shock. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Thursday condemned the killing of Benazi
